{
  "text": "\u03ea275C\u03feT is located in the CFH promoter region, which regulates CFH transcription (e.g., nuclear factor [NF]-B re- sponsive element). [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Therefore, it is possible that the function of this promoter is impaired by the presence of the T allele and that this leads to relatively lower factor H plasma levels. 18 The exon2 I62V variant is located in SCR2, which contains a regulatory domain for cofactor-and decay-accelerating activity and a binding site for C3b. [CITATION_3] 23 Furthermore, I62V is located in a predicted exon splice enhancer, and thus this polymorphism could cause splicing errors and alter CFH function and AMD development.",
  "citation_candidates": [
